  <!-- ── Prompting ── -->
  <section id="prompting">
    <div class="cgb-container">
      <p class="cgb-section-label fade-in">The Framework</p>
      <h2 class="cgb-section-title fade-in">The prompting framework</h2>
      <p class="cgb-section-intro fade-in">The quality of Copilot's output depends on how you ask. Use the <strong>GCSE framework</strong> — four ingredients that turn a vague request into a powerful prompt.</p>

      <!-- Part 1: GCSE Framework Card -->
      <div class="gcse-grid fade-in">
        <div class="gcse-item" title="Example: 'Create 5 talking points for my buyer meeting'">
          <div class="gcse-letter">G</div>
          <div class="gcse-word">Goal</div>
          <div class="gcse-desc">What you want Copilot to do</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gcse-item" title="Example: 'I'm a CPG sales rep meeting with a grocery buyer about expanding shelf space'">
          <div class="gcse-letter">C</div>
          <div class="gcse-word">Context</div>
          <div class="gcse-desc">Background, audience, or situation</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gcse-item" title="Example: 'Review /Q2-Scorecard.xlsx for sales data'">
          <div class="gcse-letter">S</div>
          <div class="gcse-word">Source</div>
          <div class="gcse-desc">Files, data, or references to use</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gcse-item" title="Example: 'Format as a numbered list, keep a professional tone, under 200 words'">
          <div class="gcse-letter">E</div>
          <div class="gcse-word">Expectations</div>
          <div class="gcse-desc">Format, tone, length, and structure</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="callout callout-tip fade-in">
        <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
        You don't need all four elements in every prompt — but the more you include, the better your results will be. Start with Goal, then add Context and Expectations as needed.
      </div>

      <!-- Part 2: Watch a Prompt Evolve -->
      <h3 class="cgb-group-heading fade-in">Watch a prompt evolve</h3>
      <p class="fade-in" style="color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:0.92rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">The same task — three levels of detail. Notice how each version layers in more GCSE elements.</p>

      <div class="evolve-stepper fade-in">
        <div class="evolve-tabs">
          <button class="evolve-tab active" data-level="good" onclick="switchEvolve('good')"><span class="evolve-dot"></span>Good</button>
          <button class="evolve-tab" data-level="better" onclick="switchEvolve('better')"><span class="evolve-dot"></span>Better</button>
          <button class="evolve-tab" data-level="best" onclick="switchEvolve('best')"><span class="evolve-dot"></span>Best</button>
        </div>
        <div class="evolve-panel-wrap">
          <div class="evolve-panel active" id="evolve-good">
            <div class="evolve-meta">
              <span class="evolve-badge good">GOOD</span>
              <div class="gcse-pills">
                <span class="gcse-pill goal">Goal</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="evolve-prompt" onclick="copyPrompt(this)"><span class="highlight-goal">Help me prepare talking points for a meeting with a grocery buyer.</span><span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            <div class="evolve-whats-new">This prompt has a clear <strong>Goal</strong>, but Copilot doesn't know who you are, what you're selling, or how to format the response — so results will be generic.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evolve-panel" id="evolve-better">
            <div class="evolve-meta">
              <span class="evolve-badge better">BETTER</span>
              <div class="gcse-pills">
                <span class="gcse-pill goal">Goal</span>
                <span class="gcse-pill context">Context</span>
                <span class="gcse-pill expectations">Expectations</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="evolve-prompt" onclick="copyPrompt(this)"><span class="highlight-context">I'm a CPG sales rep meeting with the snack category buyer at a regional grocery chain to discuss expanding our brand's shelf presence for Q3.</span> <span class="highlight-goal">Create 5 talking points covering category growth data, our brand's performance metrics, new product introductions, and promotional support we can offer.</span> <span class="highlight-expectations">Use a consultative, partnership-focused tone that positions us as a category growth partner.</span><span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            <div class="evolve-whats-new"><strong>+Context</strong> tells Copilot your role and situation. <strong>+Expectations</strong> sets the tone. Results will be more relevant and tailored to your meeting.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evolve-panel" id="evolve-best">
            <div class="evolve-meta">
              <span class="evolve-badge best">BEST</span>
              <div class="gcse-pills">
                <span class="gcse-pill goal">Goal</span>
                <span class="gcse-pill context">Context</span>
                <span class="gcse-pill source">Source</span>
                <span class="gcse-pill expectations">Expectations</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="evolve-prompt" onclick="copyPrompt(this)"><span class="highlight-context">I'm a CPG territory sales rep preparing for a quarterly category review with the snack buyer at FreshMart Grocery. Our brand holds the #2 share position in salty snacks at their stores, and we've been growing distribution across their 200-location network.</span> <span class="highlight-source">Review /FreshMart-Q2-Scorecard.xlsx for the latest sales and distribution data</span> <span class="highlight-goal">and create 5 talking points covering: category growth we've driven this quarter, our top-performing SKUs vs. plan, 2 new product launches for Q3 with projected incrementality, and one competitive gap we can help them address.</span> <span class="highlight-expectations">Format as a numbered list with a one-sentence executive summary at the top. Keep the tone confident but collaborative — this buyer values data and brevity.</span><span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            <div class="evolve-whats-new"><strong>+Source</strong> points Copilot at real data via the '/' file reference. All four GCSE elements combine for a response that's specific, data-driven, and ready to present.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gcse-legend fade-in" style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:1.5rem;font-size:0.78rem;">
        <span><span class="highlight-goal">&nbsp;Goal&nbsp;</span></span>
        <span><span class="highlight-context">&nbsp;Context&nbsp;</span></span>
        <span><span class="highlight-source">&nbsp;Source&nbsp;</span></span>
        <span><span class="highlight-expectations">&nbsp;Expectations&nbsp;</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="callout callout-tip fade-in">
        <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>You can type '/' in the prompt box to pull in any document from your Microsoft 365 files as context.
      </div>

      <!-- Part 3: Power Techniques -->
      <h3 class="cgb-group-heading fade-in">Power techniques</h3>
      <p class="fade-in" style="color:var(--text-secondary);font-size:0.92rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Six strategies that turn good prompts into great ones. Click any card to expand.</p>

      <div class="capabilities-grid prompting-techniques fade-in">
        <div class="capability-card fade-in">
          <div class="capability-header" onclick="toggleCapability(this)">
            <div class="capability-icon">🔄</div>
            <div class="capability-info"><h4>Keep the Conversation Going</h4><p class="capability-desc">Don't start over — build on what Copilot gave you with follow-up prompts.</p></div>
            <div class="expand-icon">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capability-detail"><div class="capability-detail-inner">
            <div class="prompt-example"><span class="prompt-label">First prompt:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Summarize the key consumer trends driving growth in the better-for-you snack segment for 2026.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="prompt-example" style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><span class="prompt-label">Follow-up:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Now frame those trends as talking points I can use in a category review meeting with a grocery buyer who's considering expanding our shelf space.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
              Copilot remembers your full conversation. Each follow-up refines the output — think of it as collaborating with a colleague.
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card fade-in">
          <div class="capability-header" onclick="toggleCapability(this)">
            <div class="capability-icon">📝</div>
            <div class="capability-info"><h4>Give Specific Instructions</h4><p class="capability-desc">Tell Copilot what to include AND what to leave out.</p></div>
            <div class="expand-icon">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capability-detail"><div class="capability-detail-inner">
            <div class="prompt-example"><span class="prompt-label">Try this prompt:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Write an executive summary of our brand's Q2 performance at Kroger. Focus on measurable outcomes like dollar sales growth, distribution gains, and promotional lift. Do NOT include internal margin data or broker commission details. Keep it under 200 words and suitable for sharing directly with the buyer.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
              Negative instructions ('do not include...') are surprisingly powerful — they prevent Copilot from going off-track.
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card fade-in">
          <div class="capability-header" onclick="toggleCapability(this)">
            <div class="capability-icon">📊</div>
            <div class="capability-info"><h4>Break It Into Steps</h4><p class="capability-desc">Don't cram everything into one prompt — break complex tasks into stages.</p></div>
            <div class="expand-icon">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capability-detail"><div class="capability-detail-inner">
            <div class="prompt-example"><span class="prompt-label">Step 1:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Create an outline for a quarterly business review presentation for our top retail account covering category performance, brand contribution, and growth recommendations.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="prompt-example" style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><span class="prompt-label">Step 2:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Expand the 'brand contribution' section with 3 specific examples of how our promotional programs drove incremental category sales.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="prompt-example" style="margin-top:0.75rem;"><span class="prompt-label">Step 3:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Now write speaker notes for each section in a conversational tone I can use while presenting to the buyer.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
              Multi-step prompting gives you a chance to review and course-correct at each stage — just like reviewing drafts with a teammate.
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card fade-in">
          <div class="capability-header" onclick="toggleCapability(this)">
            <div class="capability-icon">🎭</div>
            <div class="capability-info"><h4>Assign a Persona</h4><p class="capability-desc">Tell Copilot who to 'be' for more specialized, targeted answers.</p></div>
            <div class="expand-icon">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capability-detail"><div class="capability-detail-inner">
            <div class="prompt-example"><span class="prompt-label">Try this prompt:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Act as a category management consultant advising a grocery chain's VP of Merchandising. Explain in business terms why allocating more shelf space to better-for-you snack brands will drive category growth and higher basket size over the next 12 months. Keep the language retail-friendly — use terms like incrementality, penny profit, and turns.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
              Personas help set the expertise level and tone. Try 'Act as a financial analyst,' 'Act as a communications specialist,' or 'Act as an onboarding manager.'
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card fade-in">
          <div class="capability-header" onclick="toggleCapability(this)">
            <div class="capability-icon">📄</div>
            <div class="capability-info"><h4>Use Templates of Good</h4><p class="capability-desc">Give Copilot an example document to follow for structure and tone.</p></div>
            <div class="expand-icon">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capability-detail"><div class="capability-detail-inner">
            <div class="prompt-example"><span class="prompt-label">Try this prompt:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">Create a quarterly business review presentation for FreshMart Grocery's snack category buyer. Use /Kroger-QBR-Q1.pptx as a template for structure, formatting, and data visualization style. Replace all Kroger references with FreshMart details and update with Q2 data points.<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
              Uploading or referencing an existing document as a 'template of good' dramatically improves consistency — especially for proposals, reports, and customer communications.
            </div>
          </div></div>
        </div>

        <div class="capability-card fade-in">
          <div class="capability-header" onclick="toggleCapability(this)">
            <div class="capability-icon">❓</div>
            <div class="capability-info"><h4>Ask Copilot What It Needs</h4><p class="capability-desc">When you're stuck, let Copilot help you write the prompt.</p></div>
            <div class="expand-icon">+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capability-detail"><div class="capability-detail-inner">
            <div class="prompt-example"><span class="prompt-label">Try this prompt:</span>
              <div class="prompt-text" onclick="copyPrompt(this)">I need to build a new distribution pitch for a 50-store regional grocery chain that doesn't currently carry our snack brand. What specific details, data points, or context do you need from me to create the most compelling pitch?<span class="copy-hint">Click to copy</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="callout callout-tip" style="margin-top:1rem;">
              <div class="callout-title">💡 Tip</div>
              This is a power move — Copilot will ask clarifying questions that help you think through what you actually need. Great when starting from a blank page.
